## Alternativas para Interatividade

### JavaScript Puro

```vue
<template>
  <main data-page-content>
    <button id="toggle">Mostrar/Ocultar</button>
    <div id="content" style="display:none">
      <p>Conteúdo toggle</p>
    </div>
  </main>
</template>

<script setup>
if (import.meta.client) {
  document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
    const btn = document.getElementById('toggle')
    const content = document.getElementById('content')
    btn?.addEventListener('click', () => {
      content!.style.display = content!.style.display === 'none' ? 'block' : 'none'
    })
  })
}
</script>
```

### Web Components

```vue
<template>
  <main data-page-content>
    <my-counter></my-counter>
  </main>
</template>

<script setup>
if (import.meta.client && !customElements.get('my-counter')) {
  class MyCounter extends HTMLElement {
    connectedCallback() {
      let count = 0
      this.innerHTML = `
        <p>Count: <span id="c">${count}</span></p>
        <button id="inc">+</button>
      `
      this.querySelector('#inc')?.addEventListener('click', () => {
        count++
        this.querySelector('#c')!.textContent = count
      })
    }
  }
  customElements.define('my-counter', MyCounter)
}
</script>
```

---

## Tamanho do Runtime

```
Arquivo          | Size  | Gzip
-----------------|-------|------
lite.min.js      | ~12KB | ~5KB
```

Comparado ao Vue runtime:

```
Arquivo          | Size   | Gzip
-----------------|--------|-------
vue.runtime.js   | ~400KB | ~130KB
nuxt-lite        | ~12KB  | ~5KB
```

---

::callout{type="tip"}
O runtime é automaticamente injetado no HTML durante o build. Não é necessário importá-lo manualmente.
::
